{"type":"message","id":"ba999006","parentId":"c6ee3431","timestamp":"2026-03-13T22:09:43.392Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"7135eabf-d268-49f3-8920-50dcc27ae207","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- document:\n  - banner:\n    - link \"Hugging Face's logo Hugging Face\" [ref=e1]:\n      - /url: /\n      - img \"Hugging Face's logo\"\n      - text: Hugging Face\n    - textbox \"Search models, datasets, users...\" [ref=e2]\n    - navigation \"Main\" [ref=e3]:\n      - list:\n        - listitem:\n          - link \"Models\" [ref=e4]:\n            - /url: /models\n        - listitem:\n          - link \"Datasets\" [ref=e5]:\n            - /url: /datasets\n        - listitem:\n          - link \"Spaces\" [ref=e6]:\n            - /url: /spaces\n        - listitem:\n          - link \"Buckets new\" [ref=e7]:\n            - /url: /storage\n        - listitem:\n          - link \"Docs\" [ref=e8]:\n            - /url: /docs\n        - listitem:\n          - link \"Pricing\" [ref=e9]:\n            - /url: /pricing\n        - listitem:\n          - button [ref=e10]\n        - listitem:\n          - separator\n        - listitem:\n          - link \"Log In\" [ref=e11]:\n            - /url: /login\n        - listitem:\n          - link \"Sign Up\" [ref=e12]:\n            - /url: /join\n  - main:\n    - heading \"Jackrong / Qwen3.5-27B-Claude-4.6-Opus-Reasoning-Distilled like 568\" [ref=e13] [level=1]:\n      - link [ref=e14]:\n        - /url: /Jackrong\n      - link \"Jackrong\" [ref=e15]:\n        - /url: /Jackrong\n      - text: /\n      - link \"Qwen3.5-27B-Claude-4.6-Opus-Reasoning-Distilled\" [ref=e16]:\n        - /url: /Jackrong/Qwen3.5-27B-Claude-4.6-Opus-Reasoning-Distilled\n      - button \"Copy model name to clipboard\" [ref=e17]\n      - button \"like\" [ref=e18]\n      - button \"568\" [ref=e19]\n    - link \"Text Generation\" [ref=e20]:\n      - /url: /models?pipeline_tag=text-generation\n    - link \"Safetensors\" [ref=e21]:\n      - /url: /models?library=safetensors\n    - button \"nohurry/Opus-4.6-Reasoning-3000x-filtered\" [ref=e22]\n    - button \"Jackrong/Qwen3.5-reasoning-700x\" [ref=e23]\n    - link \"English\" [ref=e24]:\n      - /url: /models?language=en\n    - link \"Chinese\" [ref=e25]:\n      - /url: /models?language=zh\n    - link \"qwen3_5\" [ref=e26]:\n      - /url: /models?other=qwen3_5\n    - link \"unsloth\" [ref=e27]:\n      - /url: /models?other=unsloth\n    - link \"qwen\" [ref=e28]:\n      - /url: /models?other=qwen\n    - link \"qwen3.5\" [ref=e29]:\n      - /url: /models?other=qwen3.5\n    - link \"reasoning\" [ref=e30]:\n      - /url: /models?other=reasoning\n    - link \"chain-of-thought\" [ref=e31]:\n      - /url: /models?other=chain-of-thought\n    - link \"Dense\" [ref=e32]:\n      - /url: /models?other=Dense\n    - link \"conversational\" [ref=e33]:\n      - /url: /models?other=conversational\n    - 'button \"License: apache-2.0\"':\n      - img\n      - text: \"License: apache-2.0\"\n    - link \"Model card\" [ref=e34]:\n      - /url: /Jackrong/Qwen3.5-27B-Claude-4.6-Opus-Reasoning-Distilled\n    - link \"Files and versions xet\" [ref=e35]:\n      - /url: /Jackrong/Qwen3.5-27B-Claude-4.6-Opus-Reasoning-Distilled/tree/main\n    - link \"Community 28\" [ref=e36]:\n      - /url: /Jackrong/Qwen3.5-27B-Claude-4.6-Opus-Reasoning-Distilled/discussions\n    - button [ref=e37] [nth=1]\n    - button [ref=e38] [nth=2]\n    - heading \"🌟 Qwen3.5-27B-Claude-4.6-Opus-Reasoning-Distilled\" [ref=e39] [level=1]:\n      - link [ref=e40] [nth=1]:\n        - /url: \"#🌟-qwen35-27b-claude-46-opus-reasoning-distilled\"\n      - text: 🌟 Qwen3.5-27B-Claude-4.6-Opus-Reasoning-Distilled\n    - blockquote:\n      - paragraph:\n        - text: 📢\n        - strong: Release Note\n        - strong: \"Build Environment Upgrades:\"\n      - list:\n        - listitem:\n          - strong: Fine-tuning Framework\n          - text: \":\"\n          - strong: Unsloth 2026.3.3\n        - listitem:\n          - strong: Core Dependencies\n          - text: \":\"\n          - strong: Transformers 5.2.0\n        - listitem:\n          - text: This model fixes the crash in the official model caused by the Jinja template not supporting the\n          - strong: \"\\\"developer\\\"\"\n          - text: role. (commonly sent by modern coding agents like Claude Code and OpenCode)\n        - listitem:\n          - text: It does\n          - strong: not disable thinking mode by default\n          - text: \", and allowing the agent to run continuously for\"\n          - strong: over 9 minutes without interruption\n          - text: .\n        - listitem:\n          - text: Compared to the original model,\n          - strong: autonomy and stability are significantly improved\n          - text: .\n    - paragraph:\n      - link \"HB8AleUaMAArNyM\" [ref=e41]:\n        - /url: https://cdn-uploads.huggingface.co/production/uploads/66309bd090589b7c65950665/GHkMJL6I383eIwK1qj80K.jpeg\n        - img \"HB8AleUaMAArNyM\"\n    - heading \"💡 Model Introduction\" [ref=e42] [level=2]:\n      - link [ref=e43] [nth=2]:\n        - /url: \"#💡-model-introduction\"\n      - text: 💡 Model Introduction\n    - paragraph:\n      - strong: Qwen3.5-27B-Claude-4.6-Opus-Reasoning-Distilled\n      - text: is a highly capable reasoning model fine-tuned on top of the powerful Qwen3.5 architecture. The model's core directive is to leverage state-of-the-art Chain-of-Thought (CoT) distillation primarily sourced from Claude-4.6 Opus interactions.\n    - paragraph:\n      - text: Through Supervised Fine-Tuning (SFT) focusing specifically on structured reasoning logic, this model excels in breaking down complex user problems, planning step-by-step methodologies within strictly formatted\n      - code: <think>\n      - text: tags, and ultimately delivering precise, nuanced solutions.\n    - heading \"🧠 Example of Learned Reasoning Scaffold（Example）\" [ref=e44] [level=3]:\n      - link [ref=e45] [nth=3]:\n        - /url: \"#🧠-example-of-learned-reasoning-scaffold（example）\"\n      - text: 🧠 Example of Learned Reasoning Scaffold（Example）\n    - paragraph:\n      - text: \"The model includes targeted optimizations addressing Qwen3.5’s tendency toward excessive transitional or repetitive reasoning on simple queries. Through deep distillation and structural imitation of Claude-4.6-Opus reasoning chains, the model adopts a more efficient structured thinking pattern:\"\n      - strong: \"“Let me analyze this request carefully: 1..2..3...”.\"\n      - text: This streamlined reasoning paradigm significantly reduces redundant cognitive loops while preserving deep analytical capacity, resulting in substantially improved inference efficiency.\n    - code: \"Let me analyze this request carefully: 1. Identify the core objective of the problem. 2. Break the task into clearly defined subcomponents. 3. Evaluate constraints and edge cases. 4. Formulate a step-by-step solution plan. 5. Execute the reasoning sequentially and verify consistency. . . .\"\n    - button [ref=e46] [nth=3]\n    - heading \"🗺️ Training Pipeline Overview\" [ref=e47] [level=2]:\n      - link [ref=e48] [nth=4]:\n        - /url: \"#🗺️-training-pipeline-overview\"\n      - text: 🗺️ Training Pipeline Overview\n    - code: Base Model (Qwen3.5-27B) │ ▼ Supervised Fine-Tuning (SFT) + LoRA │ ▼ Final Model (Claude-4.6-Opus-Reasoning-Distilled,text-only)\n    - button [ref=e49] [nth=4]\n    - heading \"📋 Stage Details\" [ref=e50] [level=2]:\n      - link [ref=e51] [nth=5]:\n        - /url: \"#📋-stage-details\"\n      - text: 📋 Stage Details\n    - paragraph:\n      - text: 🔥\n      - strong: Community-tested advantages\n      - text: \"(benchmark tests by user @sudoingX on a single RTX 3090):\"\n    - paragraph: \"Qwen3.5-27B-Claude-4.6-Opus-Reasoning-Distilled shows significant advantages in coding-agent environments such as Claude Code and OpenCode:\"\n    - blockquote:\n      - list:\n        - listitem:\n          - strong: Native support for the “developer” role\n          - text: \", requiring no Jinja template patches or ChatML workarounds.\"\n        - listitem:\n          - strong: Thinking mode fully preserved\n          - text: (logs confirm\n          - code: thinking=1\n          - text: ), not silently disabled, maintaining the complete chain-of-thought reasoning process.\n        - listitem:\n          - strong: Greatly improved autonomy and stability\n          - text: — capable of running continuously for\n          - strong: over 9 minutes autonomously\n          - text: (with zero human intervention). It actively waits for tool responses, reads outputs, self-corrects errors, and can even automatically generate a README, whereas the base model often stalls or freezes mid-execution.\n    - blockquote:\n      - paragraph:\n        - strong: \"Hardware usage remains unchanged:\"\n      - list:\n        - listitem:\n          - text: About\n          - strong: 16.5 GB VRAM\n          - text: with\n          - strong: Q4_K_M\n          - text: quantization\n        - listitem:\n          - strong: 29–35 tok/s\n          - text: generation speed\n        - listitem:\n          - strong: Full 262K context\n          - text: with no compromises\n    - list:\n      - listitem:\n        - text: These improvements come from successfully distilling the\n        - strong: structured reasoning style of Claude 4.6 Opus\n        - text: \", allowing Qwopus to be truly\"\n        - strong: plug-and-play in modern local coding agents\n        - text: and deliver an experience close to Opus in smoothness and usability.\n    - paragraph:\n      - strong: Thanks to the community for the in-depth testing and feedback!\n    - heading \"🔹 Supervised Fine-Tuning (SFT)\" [ref=e52] [level=3]:\n      - link [ref=e53] [nth=6]:\n        - /url: \"#🔹-supervised-fine-tuning-sft\"\n      - text: 🔹 Supervised Fine-Tuning (SFT)\n    - list:\n      - listitem:\n        - strong: \"Objective:\"\n        - text: To inject high-density reasoning logic and establish a strict format for problem-solving involving an internal thinking state prior to outputting the final response.\n      - listitem:\n        - strong: \"Methodology:\"\n        - text: We utilized\n        - strong: Unsloth\n        - text: for highly efficient memory and compute optimization. A critical component of this stage is the\n        - code: train_on_responses_only\n        - text: strategy, masking instructions so the loss is purely calculated over the generation of the\n        - code: <think>\n        - text: sequences and the subsequent solutions.\n      - listitem:\n        - strong: \"Format Enforcement:\"\n        - text: All training samples were systematically normalized so the model strictly abides by the structure\n        - code: \"<think> {internal reasoning} </think>\\\\n {final answer}\"\n        - text: .\n    - heading \"📚 All Datasets Used\" [ref=e54] [level=3]:\n      - link [ref=e55] [nth=7]:\n        - /url: \"#📚-all-datasets-used\"\n      - text: 📚 All Datasets Used\n    - paragraph: \"The dataset consists of high-quality, filtered reasoning distillation data:\"\n    - table:\n      - rowgroup:\n        - row \"Dataset Name Description / Purpose\":\n          - columnheader \"Dataset Name\" [ref=e56]\n          - columnheader \"Description / Purpose\" [ref=e57]\n      - rowgroup:\n        - row \"nohurry/Opus-4.6-Reasoning-3000x-filtered Provides comprehensive Claude 4.6 Opus reasoning trajectories.\":\n          - cell \"nohurry/Opus-4.6-Reasoning-3000x-filtered\" [ref=e58]:\n            - link \"nohurry/Opus-4.6-Reasoning-3000x-filtered\" [ref=e59]:\n              - /url: https://huggingface.co/datasets/nohurry/Opus-4.6-Reasoning-3000x-filtered\n          - cell \"Provides comprehensive Claude 4.6 Opus reasoning trajectories.\" [ref=e60]\n        - row \"TeichAI/claude-4.5-opus-high-reasoning-250x Injecting high-intensity, structured reasoning instances.\":\n          - cell \"TeichAI/claude-4.5-opus-high-reasoning-250x\" [ref=e61]:\n            - link \"TeichAI/claude-4.5-opus-high-reasoning-250x\" [ref=e62]:\n              - /url: https://huggingface.co/datasets/TeichAI/claude-4.5-opus-high-reasoning-250x\n          - cell \"Injecting high-intensity, structured reasoning instances.\" [ref=e63]\n        - row \"Jackrong/Qwen3.5-reasoning-700x Additional curated reasoning samples designed to strengthen structured step-by-step problem solving and improve reasoning diversity.\":\n          - cell \"Jackrong/Qwen3.5-reasoning-700x\" [ref=e64]:\n            - link \"Jackrong/Qwen3.5-reasoning-700x\" [ref=e65]:\n              - /url: https://huggingface.co/datasets/Jackrong/Qwen3.5-reasoning-700x\n          - cell \"Additional curated reasoning samples designed to strengthen structured step-by-step problem solving and improve reasoning diversity.\" [ref=e66]\n    - heading \"🌟 Core Skills & Capabilities\" [ref=e67] [level=2]:\n      - link [ref=e68] [nth=8]:\n        - /url: \"#🌟-core-skills--capabilities\"\n      - text: 🌟 Core Skills & Capabilities\n    - list:\n      - listitem:\n        - strong: \"Modular & Structured Thinking:\"\n        - text: Inheriting traits from Opus-level reasoning, the model demonstrates confident parsing of the prompt, establishing an outlined plan in its\n        - code: <think>\n        - text: block sequentially rather than exploratory \"trial-and-error\" self-doubt.\n    - heading \"⚠️ Limitations & Intended Use\" [ref=e69] [level=2]:\n      - link [ref=e70] [nth=9]:\n        - /url: \"#⚠️-limitations--intended-use\"\n      - text: ⚠️ Limitations & Intended Use\n    - list:\n      - listitem:\n        - strong: \"Hallucination Risk:\"\n        - text: While reasoning is strong, the model remains an autoregressive LLM; external facts provided during the thinking sequence may occasionally contain hallucinations if verifying real-world events.\n      - listitem:\n        - strong: \"Intended Scenario:\"\n        - text: Best suited for offline analytical tasks, coding, math, and heavy logic-dependent prompting where the user needs to transparently follow the AI's internal logic.\n      - listitem:\n        - strong: \"Preview Version Notice:\"\n        - text: Because this model is relatively new and intentionally lightweight, the surrounding ecosystem — including inference templates, fine-tuning pipelines, routing configurations, and tooling integrations — may not yet be fully mature or standardized. As a result, users may encounter occasional bugs, compatibility inconsistencies, or integration edge cases. The current release should be considered a preview build while the broader architectural stack and supporting utilities continue to stabilize and improve.\n    - heading \"🙏 Acknowledgements\" [ref=e71] [level=2]:\n      - link [ref=e72] [nth=10]:\n        - /url: \"#🙏-acknowledgements\"\n      - text: 🙏 Acknowledgements\n    - paragraph:\n      - text: Significant thanks to the\n      - link \"Unsloth AI\" [ref=e73]:\n        - /url: https://unsloth.ai/\n      - text: team for making rapid fine-tuning of MoE and large LLM models accessible. Additionally, we acknowledge Qwen internally, and the open-source community developers producing exceptional distilled datasets (\n      - code: nohurry\n      - text: and\n      - code: TeichAI\n      - text: ).\n    - heading \"📖 Citation\" [ref=e74] [level=2]:\n      - link [ref=e75] [nth=11]:\n        - /url: \"#📖-citation\"\n      - text: 📖 Citation\n    - paragraph: \"If you use this model in your research or projects, please cite:\"\n    - code: \"@misc{jackrong_qwen35_opus_distilled, title = {Qwen3.5-27B-Claude-4.6-Opus-Reasoning-Distilled}, author = {Jackrong}, year = {2026}, publisher = {Hugging Face}, howpublished = {\\\\url{https://huggingface.co/Jackrong/Qwen3.5-27B-Claude-4.6-Opus-Reasoning-Distilled}} }\"\n    - button [ref=e76] [nth=5]\n    - term: Downloads last month\n    - definition: 53,243\n    - img\n    - text: Safetensors\n    - link [ref=e77] [nth=12]:\n      - /url: https://huggingface.co/docs/safetensors\n    - text: Model size 28B params Tensor type BF16 · F32\n    - button \"Chat template\" [ref=e78]:\n      - paragraph: Chat template\n    - button \"Files info\" [ref=e79]:\n      - paragraph: Files info\n    - text: Inference Providers\n    - link \"NEW\" [ref=e80]:\n      - /url: https://huggingface.co/docs/inference-providers\n    - link \"Text Generation\" [ref=e81] [nth=1]:\n      - /url: /tasks/text-generation\n    - text: This model isn't deployed by any Inference Provider.\n    - link \"🙋 15 Ask for provider support\" [ref=e82]:\n      - /url: /spaces/huggingface/InferenceSupport/discussions/8444\n    - heading \"Model tree for Jackrong/Qwen3.5-27B-Claude-4.6-Opus-Reasoning-Distilled\" [ref=e83] [level=2]:\n      - text: Model tree for Jackrong/Qwen3.5-27B-Claude-4.6-Opus-Reasoning-Distilled\n      - link [ref=e84] [nth=13]:\n        - /url: /docs/hub/model-cards#specifying-a-base-model\n    - paragraph: Base model\n    - link \"Qwen/Qwen3.5-27B\" [ref=e85]:\n      - /url: /Qwen/Qwen3.5-27B\n    - img\n    - text: Finetuned (\n    - link \"66\" [ref=e86]:\n      - /url: /models?other=base_model:finetune:Qwen/Qwen3.5-27B\n    - text: ) this model\n    - img\n    - text: Adapters\n    - link \"1 model\" [ref=e87]:\n      - /url: /models?other=base_model:adapter:Jackrong/Qwen3.5-27B-Claude-4.6-Opus-Reasoning-Distilled\n    - img\n    - text: Finetunes\n    - link \"2 models\" [ref=e88]:\n      - /url: /models?other=base_model:finetune:Jackrong/Qwen3.5-27B-Claude-4.6-Opus-Reasoning-Distilled\n    - img\n    - text: Quantizations\n    - link \"Use with llama.cpp\" [ref=e89]:\n      - /url: /models?apps=llama.cpp&other=base_model:quantized:Jackrong/Qwen3.5-27B-Claude-4.6-Opus-Reasoning-Distilled\n    - link \"Use with LM Studio\" [ref=e90]:\n      - /url: /models?apps=lmstudio&other=base_model:quantized:Jackrong/Qwen3.5-27B-Claude-4.6-Opus-Reasoning-Distilled\n    - link \"Use with Jan\" [ref=e91]:\n      - /url: /models?apps=jan&other=base_model:quantized:Jackrong/Qwen3.5-27B-Claude-4.6-Opus-Reasoning-Distilled\n    - link \"Use with Ollama\" [ref=e92]:\n      - /url: /models?apps=ollama&other=base_model:quantized:Jackrong/Qwen3.5-27B-Claude-4.6-Opus-Reasoning-Distilled\n    - link \"17 models\" [ref=e93]:\n      - /url: /models?other=base_model:quantized:Jackrong/Qwen3.5-27B-Claude-4.6-Opus-Reasoning-Distilled\n    - heading \"Datasets used to train Jackrong/Qwen3.5-27B-Claude-4.6-Opus-Reasoning-Distilled\" [ref=e94] [level=2]\n    - navigation:\n      - article:\n        - link \"nohurry/Opus-4.6-Reasoning-3000x-filtered Viewer • Updated Feb 10 • 2.33k • 4.27k • 339\" [ref=e95]:\n          - /url: /datasets/nohurry/Opus-4.6-Reasoning-3000x-filtered\n          - heading \"nohurry/Opus-4.6-Reasoning-3000x-filtered\" [ref=e96] [level=4]\n          - text: Viewer • Updated\n          - time: Feb 10\n          - text: • 2.33k • 4.27k • 339\n      - article:\n        - link \"Jackrong/Qwen3.5-reasoning-700x Viewer • Updated 11 days ago • 633 • 529 • 37\" [ref=e97]:\n          - /url: /datasets/Jackrong/Qwen3.5-reasoning-700x\n          - heading \"Jackrong/Qwen3.5-reasoning-700x\" [ref=e98] [level=4]\n          - text: Viewer • Updated\n          - time: 11 days ago\n          - text: • 633 • 529 • 37\n    - heading \"Spaces using Jackrong/Qwen3.5-27B-Claude-4.6-Opus-Reasoning-Distilled 2\" [ref=e99] [level=2]\n    - navigation:\n      - link \"💻 Matrix-Corp/ECHO\" [ref=e100]:\n        - /url: /spaces/Matrix-Corp/ECHO\n      - link \"💬 Laksh99/Qwen_new\" [ref=e101]:\n        - /url: /spaces/Laksh99/Qwen_new\n    - heading \"Collection including Jackrong/Qwen3.5-27B-Claude-4.6-Opus-Reasoning-Distilled\" [ref=e102] [level=2]\n    - article:\n      - link \"Qwen3.5-Claude-4.6-Opus-Reasoning-Distilled Collection 18 items • Updated 3 days ago • 64\" [ref=e103]:\n        - /url: /collections/Jackrong/qwen35-claude-46-opus-reasoning-