{"type":"message","id":"a9061d80","parentId":"6fbee5db","timestamp":"2026-03-14T10:44:51.996Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK I've read through the releases page thoroughly. I can see three releases on this page:\n\n1. **openclaw 2026.3.13** (Latest) - The latest release. The changes are truncated, but I can see it includes various changes.\n\n2. **openclaw 2026.3.7-beta.1** (Pre-release) - Various changes.\n\n3. **openclaw 2026.3.2** - Has several Chrome/browser related items:\n   - \"Browser/CDP startup diagnostics: include Chrome stderr output and a Linux no-sandbox hint in startup timeout errors so failed launches are easier to diagnose. (#29312)\" - This is a fix!\n   - Also mentions onboarding/headless Linux daemon probe hardening\n\nLooking at the latest 2026.3.13 release, I need to get the full details since the content is truncated. I'm particularly interested in finding the Chrome 146 update that the user mentioned, and I can see some references to `@obviyus` in the changes list. Let me focus on extracting the complete release notes for 2026.3.13 to identify all Chrome-related modifications.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me get the full latest release notes directly."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"b8cebf2c-a1dd-4f17-8148-09c8fd96ef31","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"agent-browser get text @e126 2>&1","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/hunter-alpha","usage":{"input":49502,"output":571,"cacheRead":131520,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":181593,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773485076919}}
