{"type":"message","id":"ba0c7fdf","parentId":"59e0d232","timestamp":"2026-03-14T10:45:49.618Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Confirmed running 2026.3.13. Now let me test the new Chrome-related features. Let me try:\n1. The new `profile=\"user\"` for the logged-in host browser\n2. The browser act automation with batched actions\n3. The new Chrome DevTools MCP attach mode\n\nLet me test using the browser tool with the new profile options.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Running 2026.3.13. Let me test the new Chrome/browser features from this release.\n\n**New Chrome features in 2026.3.13:**\n1. `profile=\"user\"` — use the logged-in host browser\n2. `profile=\"chrome-relay\"` — Chrome extension relay\n3. Browser act batched actions, selector targeting, delayed clicks\n4. Chrome DevTools MCP attach mode for live sessions\n5. Hardened driver validation & session lifecycle\n\nLet me test the batched browser actions:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"f941449b-d521-4e32-a32a-4fa10a450e75","name":"browser","arguments":{"action":"open","profile":"user","url":"https://nxguen5lrkrca.ok.kimi.link/"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/hunter-alpha","usage":{"input":154,"output":327,"cacheRead":183296,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":183777,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773485140623}}
{"type":"message","id":"c5ceb021","parentId":"ba0c7fdf","timestamp":"2026-03-14T10:45:52.078Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"f941449b-d521-4e32-a32a-4fa10a450e75","toolName":"browser","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"status\": \"error\",\n  \"tool\": \"browser\",\n  \"error\": \"Error: Could not connect to Chrome. Check if Chrome is running.\\nCause: Could not find DevToolsActivePort for chrome at /home/pete/.config/google-chrome/DevToolsActivePort\"\n}"}],"details":{"status":"error","tool":"browser","error":"Error: Could not connect to Chrome. Check if Chrome is running.\nCause: Could not find DevToolsActivePort for chrome at /home/pete/.config/google-chrome/DevToolsActivePort"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773485152075}}
{"type":"message","id":"3ddf76b9","parentId":"c5ceb021","timestamp":"2026-03-14T10:46:02.994Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"`profile=\"user\"` tries to connect to the user's logged-in Chrome. Chrome isn't running with remote debugging on this machine. That's expected behavior — the feature works but needs Chrome running with `--remote-debugging-port` or the `chrome://inspect/#remote-debugging` flag. Let me test the default profile which uses the OpenClaw-managed browser.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Expected — `profile=\"user\"` needs Chrome running with remote debugging enabled. Let me test with the default managed browser and try the batched actions feature:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"7d9e7102-325b-4025-be81-e36bdfdd0325","name":"browser","arguments":{"action":"open","url":"https://nxguen5lrkrca.ok.kimi.link/"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/hunter-alpha","usage":{"input":346,"output":239,"cacheRead":183424,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":184009,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773485152084}}
