{"type":"message","id":"52b6331c","parentId":"aacd311a","timestamp":"2026-03-14T10:55:19.832Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see there's a Chrome crashpad handler running from the user's config directory, but the main Chrome binary path shows `/Home1/google/chrome/chrome` for the OpenClaw-managed browser. The user's Chrome is at version 144.0.7559.109 (from crashpad annotation), while the OpenClaw one is 146.\n\nThe user says they enabled `chrome://inspect/#remote-debugging` in their running Chrome. This is a setting within Chrome that allows remote debugging. But for this to work, Chrome needs to be launched with `--remote-debugging-port` flag, OR the user needs to have a separate Chrome instance running with that flag.\n\nLet me check if there's a separate user Chrome process with a debugging port.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"187604e3-d063-421c-b0cd-6cf59255fef5","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check for any Chrome with remote debugging besides OpenClaw's\nss -tlnp 2>/dev/null | grep -E \"922[0-9]|923[0-9]\"; \\\n# Check DevToolsActivePort in the openclaw browser dir\ncat /home/pete/.openclaw/browser/openclaw/user-data/DevToolsActivePort 2>&1; \\\n# Try connecting to OpenClaw's Chrome directly\ncurl -s http://127.0.0.1:18800/json/version 2>&1 | head -20","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/hunter-alpha","usage":{"input":776,"output":498,"cacheRead":193472,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":194746,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773485695999}}
