{"type":"message","id":"82c8ee82","parentId":"6cb483ce","timestamp":"2026-03-14T10:55:30.586Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! The OpenClaw Chrome is actually version 144.0.7559.109, not 146. So the Chrome 146 that agent-browser installed is separate. The OpenClaw browser is already running on port 18800 and responding to CDP requests.\n\nThe `profile=\"user\"` feature is looking for the DevToolsActivePort file at `/home/pete/.config/google-chrome/DevToolsActivePort`, which doesn't exist because the user's main Chrome isn't launched with `--remote-debugging-port`.\n\nThe `chrome://inspect/#remote-debugging` setting within Chrome is different from launching with `--remote-debugging-port`. The in-Chrome setting enables the inspect page but doesn't automatically open a debugging port.\n\n\nSo when Matt mentioned enabling `chrome://inspect/#remote-debugging`, he likely meant he opened that page in the OpenClaw-managed Chrome and enabled the discover feature, or he launched a separate Chrome with remote debugging. Either way, I should try connecting directly to that CDP port at 18800 with the `profile=\"openclaw\"` setting, since that's already working with the OpenClaw browser.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"d41e5499-9258-44f5-8345-7cee64e7bb9d","name":"browser","arguments":{"action":"navigate","profile":"openclaw","url":"https://nxguen5lrkrca.ok.kimi.link/"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/hunter-alpha","usage":{"input":592,"output":580,"cacheRead":194240,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":195412,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773485720009}}
