{"type":"message","id":"e8598c6a","parentId":"7aca221a","timestamp":"2026-03-14T10:56:14.665Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The OpenClaw browser tool with `profile=\"openclaw\"` is working perfectly. The snapshot is clean and detailed with ARIA refs.\n\nNow, regarding `profile=\"user\"` — the issue is that Chrome needs to be launched by the user with `--remote-debugging-port=9222` for the DevToolsActivePort file to be created. The `chrome://inspect/#remote-debugging` setting within Chrome doesn't automatically open a debugging port — it just enables the inspect UI.\n\nLet me explain this to Matt and show him what's working.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"There it is — clean snapshot with full ARIA refs. The OpenClaw browser (`profile=\"openclaw\"`) is working great.\n\nAbout `profile=\"user\"` — here's what's happening:\n\nThe `chrome://inspect/#remote-debugging` page in Chrome is the **inspect UI**, but it doesn't open a debugging port itself. For `profile=\"user\"` to work, Chrome needs to be launched with an explicit `--remote-debugging-port` flag, which creates the `DevToolsActivePort` file that OpenClaw looks for.\n\nYour current Chrome setup:\n- **OpenClaw managed Chrome** (port 18800) → ✅ Working with `profile=\"openclaw\"`\n- **User Chrome** (`~/.config/google-chrome/`) → No `DevToolsActivePort` file, so `profile=\"user\"` can't attach\n\nTo make `profile=\"user\"` work, you'd need to either:\n\n1. **Launch Chrome with debugging:** `/usr/bin/google-chrome --remote-debugging-port=9222`\n2. **Or use the existing OpenClaw Chrome** (which is already running on port 18800) — that's what `profile=\"openclaw\"` does, and it's already working\n\nThe new `profile=\"user\"` and `profile=\"chrome-relay\"` features in 2026.3.13 are designed for scenarios like:\n- **`profile=\"user\"`**: You have Chrome running separately and want to reuse your Gmail/Google logged-in sessions\n- **`profile=\"chrome-relay\"`**: You want to attach to a specific tab via the Chrome extension toolbar button\n\nBoth `agent-browser` CLI and the OpenClaw `browser` tool are fully functional on this machine. 🦞"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/hunter-alpha","usage":{"input":4185,"output":623,"cacheRead":195456,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":200264,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773485759847}}
