{"type":"message","id":"1cde6782","parentId":"3cb65ac6","timestamp":"2026-03-14T11:04:26.650Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Now let me summarize. The `profile=\"user\"` feature works when Chrome is running with remote debugging. The DevToolsActivePort file is the key — if Chrome doesn't create it automatically (which this version seems not to), you can create it manually pointing to the actual port and WebSocket URL.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"**Summary of `profile=\"user\"` test:**\n\n| Step | Result |\n|------|--------|\n| Launch Chrome with `--remote-debugging-port=9222` | ✅ Running |\n| Create `DevToolsActivePort` file manually | ✅ (Chrome didn't auto-create it) |\n| `browser` tool with `profile=\"user\"` | ✅ Connected |\n| Navigate to page | ✅ |\n| Snapshot with ARIA refs | ✅ Clean |\n\nThe new `profile=\"user\"` feature in 2026.3.13 works. One caveat: Chrome 144 on this system doesn't auto-create `DevToolsActivePort` when launched manually — we had to create it ourselves at `~/.config/google-chrome/DevToolsActivePort` with the port and WebSocket path. Once that file exists, OpenClaw attaches seamlessly to the user's logged-in Chrome sessions."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/hunter-alpha","usage":{"input":266,"output":332,"cacheRead":205376,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":205974,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773486258678}}
{"type":"message","id":"9ae9579c","parentId":"1cde6782","timestamp":"2026-03-14T11:09:29.796Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-03-14 19:02:57 GMT+8] Exec failed (lucky-wi, code 0) :: apis/gcm/engine/registration_request.cc:291] Registration response error message: DEPRECATED_ENDPOINT [533046:533074:0314/190104.523245:ERROR:google_apis/gcm/engine/registration_r…\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Sat 2026-03-14 19:09 GMT+8] awesome findings about the new Chrome features in the latest OpenClaw release. Now, please carefully record your new insights about the new Chrome features and the gotchas in your long term context memory so that you remember to use all the browser capabilities in future."}],"timestamp":1773486569785}}
{"type":"message","id":"a9cebe00","parentId":"9ae9579c","timestamp":"2026-03-14T11:09:53.580Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Matt wants me to update MEMORY.md with the new Chrome/browser findings from the 2026.3.13 release, including the gotchas we discovered during testing.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"2aca4339-2a9d-4b3a-8313-a8522859415f","name":"edit","arguments":{"new_string":"## Browser Automation — agent-browser\n\n**Status:** ✅ v0.20.0 | Chrome 146 installed | `--no-sandbox` set in `~/.agent-browser/config.json`\n\n```bash\nagent-browser open <url>              # Navigate\nagent-browser snapshot -i             # Interactive tree with refs (@e1, @e2, ...)\nagent-browser click @e2 / fill @e3 \"text\"  # Interact by ref\nagent-browser screenshot [path]       # Screenshot\nagent-browser eval \"document.title\"   # Run JS\nagent-browser get title / url / text @ref  # Query page\nagent-browser close                   # Done\n```\n\n**Config:** `~/.agent-browser/config.json` has `{\"args\": \"--no-sandbox\"}` (Ubuntu AppArmor requirement)\n**Howto:** `/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/Agent-Browser-howto.md`\n**Notes:** Prefer `snapshot -i` with refs over CSS selectors. Daemon auto-starts. Chrome at `~/.agent-browser/browsers/`.\n\n## OpenClaw Browser Tool (built-in)\n\n**Status:** ✅ Verified working (2026.3.14) | Chrome 144 on port 18800\n\n### Profiles (new in 2026.3.13)\n- **`profile=\"openclaw\"`** — Default managed Chrome. Works out of the box. Port 18800.\n- **`profile=\"user\"`** — Attaches to user's logged-in Chrome. Needs `DevToolsActivePort` file.\n- **`profile=\"chrome-relay\"`** — Chrome extension relay for specific tab attach.\n\n### `profile=\"user\"` Gotchas (CRITICAL)\n- Looks for `DevToolsActivePort` at `~/.config/google-chrome/DevToolsActivePort`\n- Launch Chrome: `/usr/bin/google-chrome --remote-debugging-port=9222 --user-data-dir=/tmp/chrome-user-profile`\n- Chrome 144 may NOT auto-create `DevToolsActivePort` — create manually:\n  ```bash\n  echo \"9222\" > ~/.config/google-chrome/DevToolsActivePort\n  echo \"/devtools/browser/<ws-uuid>\" >> ~/.config/google-chrome/DevToolsActivePort\n  ```\n  Get the WebSocket UUID from: `curl -s http://127.0.0.1:9222/json/version`\n- If Chrome uses same user-data-dir as existing instance, port won't bind — use separate `--user-data-dir`\n- Cannot navigate to `chrome://` URLs through the browser tool (blocked)\n\n### New 2026.3.13 Features\n- Batched browser actions via `act` request (selector targeting, delayed clicks)\n- Hardened session lifecycle (transport errors → reconnect, tool errors → preserve session)\n- Shared ARIA role sets between Playwright and Chrome MCP snapshots\n\n### Quick Reference\n```bash\n# Built-in browser tool (OpenClaw)\nbrowser open <url>                    # Navigate (default profile)\nbrowser snapshot -i                   # Snapshot with refs\nbrowser snapshot --profile user       # Use logged-in Chrome\nbrowser act <action>                  # Single or batched actions\n\n# agent-browser CLI\nagent-browser open <url>              # Navigate\nagent-browser snapshot -i             # Interactive tree\n```\n\n**Howto:** `/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/Agent-Browser-howto.md`\n**Chrome:** Both agent-browser (Chrome 146) and OpenClaw built-in (Chrome 144) available","old_string":"## Browser Automation — agent-browser\n\n**Status:** ✅ v0.20.0 | Chrome 146 installed | `--no-sandbox` set in `~/.agent-browser/config.json`\n\n```bash\nagent-browser open <url>              # Navigate\nagent-browser snapshot -i             # Interactive tree with refs (@e1, @e2, ...)\nagent-browser click @e2 / fill @e3 \"text\"  # Interact by ref\nagent-browser screenshot [path]       # Screenshot\nagent-browser eval \"document.title\"   # Run JS\nagent-browser get title / url / text @ref  # Query page\nagent-browser close                   # Done\n```\n\n**Config:** `~/.agent-browser/config.json` has `{\"args\": \"--no-sandbox\"}` (Ubuntu AppArmor requirement)\n**Howto:** `/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/Agent-Browser-howto.md`\n**Notes:** Prefer `snapshot -i` with refs over CSS selectors. Daemon auto-starts. Chrome at `~/.agent-browser/browsers/`.","path":"/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/hunter-alpha","usage":{"input":510,"output":1113,"cacheRead":205632,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":207255,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773486569790}}
{"type":"message","id":"bedac948","parentId":"a9cebe00","timestamp":"2026-03-14T11:09:53.600Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"2aca4339-2a9d-4b3a-8313-a8522859415f","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 139 **Config:** `~/.agent-browser/config.json` has `{\"args\": \"--no-sandbox\"}` (Ubuntu AppArmor requirement)\n 140 **Howto:** `/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/Agent-Browser-howto.md`\n 141 **Notes:** Prefer `snapshot -i` with refs over CSS selectors. Daemon auto-starts. Chrome at `~/.agent-browser/browsers/`.\n 142 \n+143 ## OpenClaw Browser Tool (built-in)\n+144 \n+145 **Status:** ✅ Verified working (2026.3.14) | Chrome 144 on port 18800\n+146 \n+147 ### Profiles (new in 2026.3.13)\n+148 - **`profile=\"openclaw\"`** — Default managed Chrome. Works out of the box. Port 18800.\n+149 - **`profile=\"user\"`** — Attaches to user's logged-in Chrome. Needs `DevToolsActivePort` file.\n+150 - **`profile=\"chrome-relay\"`** — Chrome extension relay for specific tab attach.\n+151 \n+152 ### `profile=\"user\"` Gotchas (CRITICAL)\n+153 - Looks for `DevToolsActivePort` at `~/.config/google-chrome/DevToolsActivePort`\n+154 - Launch Chrome: `/usr/bin/google-chrome --remote-debugging-port=9222 --user-data-dir=/tmp/chrome-user-profile`\n+155 - Chrome 144 may NOT auto-create `DevToolsActivePort` — create manually:\n+156   ```bash\n+157   echo \"9222\" > ~/.config/google-chrome/DevToolsActivePort\n+158   echo \"/devtools/browser/<ws-uuid>\" >> ~/.config/google-chrome/DevToolsActivePort\n+159   ```\n+160   Get the WebSocket UUID from: `curl -s http://127.0.0.1:9222/json/version`\n+161 - If Chrome uses same user-data-dir as existing instance, port won't bind — use separate `--user-data-dir`\n+162 - Cannot navigate to `chrome://` URLs through the browser tool (blocked)\n+163 \n+164 ### New 2026.3.13 Features\n+165 - Batched browser actions via `act` request (selector targeting, delayed clicks)\n+166 - Hardened session lifecycle (transport errors → reconnect, tool errors → preserve session)\n+167 - Shared ARIA role sets between Playwright and Chrome MCP snapshots\n+168 \n+169 ### Quick Reference\n+170 ```bash\n+171 # Built-in browser tool (OpenClaw)\n+172 browser open <url>                    # Navigate (default profile)\n+173 browser snapshot -i                   # Snapshot with refs\n+174 browser snapshot --profile user       # Use logged-in Chrome\n+175 browser act <action>                  # Single or batched actions\n+176 \n+177 # agent-browser CLI\n+178 agent-browser open <url>              # Navigate\n+179 agent-browser snapshot -i             # Interactive tree\n+180 ```\n+181 \n+182 **Howto:** `/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/Agent-Browser-howto.md`\n+183 **Chrome:** Both agent-browser (Chrome 146) and OpenClaw built-in (Chrome 144) available\n+184 \n 143 ## E2E Testing Lessons\n 144 \n 145 **Skill:** `/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/skills/e2e-testing-lessons/SKILL.md`\n 146 **Source:** LedgerSG 15-phase E2E report (2026-03-14)\n     ...","firstChangedLine":143},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773486593598}}
