{"type":"message","id":"d54025c0","parentId":"230b2d22","timestamp":"2026-03-14T11:09:58.044Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"807b300d-cd02-428b-ad88-fac83218209c","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-03-14 (Saturday)\n\n## agent-browser Tool Verification (05:56 SGT)\n\n- Reviewed `/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/Agent-Browser-howto.md` — comprehensive CLI reference for agent-browser v0.19.0\n- Ran `agent-browser install --with-deps` to set up Chromium browser (system deps already present)\n- Tested browsing `https://nxguen5lrkrca.ok.kimi.link/` — AI Academy landing page\n- Verified `snapshot -i` returns full interactive element tree with refs\n- Verified `screenshot` works (saved to `/tmp/agent-browser-test.png`)\n- **Result:** Tool is fully functional, recorded in MEMORY.md\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773486598042}}
{"type":"message","id":"1a891795","parentId":"d54025c0","timestamp":"2026-03-14T11:10:13.750Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me add today's findings to the daily notes.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"fc8ebbe2-dc8a-415f-a15a-3f9dfc05a1ee","name":"edit","arguments":{"new_string":"- **Result:** Tool is fully functional, recorded in MEMORY.md\n\n## agent-browser v0.20.0 Upgrade (10:27 SGT)\n\n- Updated via `npm install agent-browser` — now v0.20.0\n- Chrome 146 installed to `~/.agent-browser/browsers/chrome-146.0.7680.80`\n- Chrome 146 on Ubuntu requires `--no-sandbox` (AppArmor restriction)\n- Set permanently in `~/.agent-browser/config.json`: `{\"args\": \"--no-sandbox\"}`\n- All 13 tests passed: open, snapshot, screenshot, get, fill, is, eval, scroll, navigate, back/forward, close\n\n## OpenClaw 2026.3.13 Release Review (18:43 SGT)\n\n- Matt upgraded OpenClaw to 2026.3.13\n- Reviewed release notes on GitHub for Chrome-related features\n- New Chrome features: `profile=\"user\"`, `profile=\"chrome-relay\"`, batched actions, hardened session lifecycle\n- Tested `profile=\"user\"` — needs `DevToolsActivePort` file\n- Discovered Chrome 144 doesn't auto-create `DevToolsActivePort` when launched with `--remote-debugging-port`\n- Workaround: create the file manually with port + WebSocket UUID\n- Both `agent-browser` CLI and OpenClaw `browser` tool fully verified working\n- Created skill file: `/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/skills/e2e-testing-lessons/SKILL.md`\n\n## E2E Testing Lessons Skill (14:55 SGT)\n\n- Reviewed `/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/E2E_TESTING_EXPERIENCE_REPORT.md` (LedgerSG, 15 phases)\n- Created condensed skill at `/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/skills/e2e-testing-lessons/SKILL.md`\n- Key lesson: Hybrid API+UI pattern — API for auth/data, UI for visual proof only\n- HttpOnly cookies break automation; always authenticate via API in tests","old_string":"- **Result:** Tool is fully functional, recorded in MEMORY.md","path":"/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026/03/14.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/hunter-alpha","usage":{"input":242,"output":549,"cacheRead":207232,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":208023,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773486598048}}
